'''Tōka Ebisu Shrine''' (十日恵比須神社[[ja:十日恵比須神社]]) is a [[shrine]] located in {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}}, {{ill|Fukuoka City|ja|福岡市}}, {{ill|Hakata Ward|ja|博多区}} {{Efn|法人番号：2290005000477<ref name = "houjin-bangou">{{Cite web|和書| author = 国税庁長官官房企画課法人番号管理室 | url = https://www.houjin-bangou.nta.go.jp/ | title = 国税庁法人番号公表サイト | accessdate = 2022-10-30 }}→検索</ref>}}. It enshrines {{ill|Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|ja|事代主命}} (Ebisu) and {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主命}} (Daikoku).

== History ==
According to the shrine's tradition<ref>[http://www.tooka-ebisu.or.jp/history.html About Tōka Ebisu] Tōka Ebisu Shrine</ref>, Takeuchi Goemon (Heijiro) of the Kashiigu Ōmiya clan, who operated a business under the name "Kamiya" in Hakata, found two divine images of Ebisu that had washed ashore at Kashiihama while visiting {{ill|Kashiigu|ja|香椎宮}} and {{ill|Hakozaki Shrine|ja|筥崎宮}} on January 3, 19th year of {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正}} ({{ill|1591|ja|1591年}}). He brought them home and enshrined them, leading to his family's prosperity. The following year, on January 10, 1st year of {{ill|Bunroku|ja|文禄}} ({{ill|1592|ja|1592年}}), Heijiro built a shrine at the place where he found the divine images. Later, on November 15, 1st year of {{ill|Tenna (Japan)|ja|天和}} ({{ill|1681|ja|1681年}}), the fourth-generation Heijiro rebuilt the shrine within the grounds of Sōfukuji Temple in Chiyo to commemorate the 90th anniversary of its founding.

In October of the 12th year of {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治}} ({{ill|1879|ja|1879年}}), the shrine was relocated to {{ill|Higashi Park (Fukuoka)|ja|東公園}} by order of Fukuoka Prefecture. In the 4th year of {{ill|Shōwa|ja|昭和}} ({{ill|1929|ja|1929年}}), it was moved to its current location due to the redevelopment of Higashi Park. In the 43rd year of Shōwa ({{ill|1968|ja|1968年}}), it was included in the list of Beppyo shrines.

== Facilities ==
The main facilities within the shrine grounds are as follows:
{{columns-list|3|
*[[Shrine architecture|Shrine building]] (a combined worship and main hall)
*Shrine office
*{{ill|Chōzuya|ja|手水舎}}
*{{ill|Torii|ja|鳥居}}
*Lion-dogs (Shishi and Komainu)
}}
<gallery>
File:Tōka-ebisu Jinja shintō shrine haiden 7-1 Higashikōen Hakata-ku Fukuoka City 20221115.jpg|Worship hall
File:Tōka-ebisu Jinja shintō shrine honden 7-1 Higashikōen Hakata-ku Fukuoka City 20221115.jpg|Main hall
</gallery>

== Tōka Ebisu New Year's Festival ==
Every year, a grand festival is held from {{ill|January 8|ja|1月8日}} to {{ill|January 11|ja|1月11日}}. The 8th is called "Hatsu Ebisu," the 9th is "Yoi Ebisu," the 10th is the "Main Festival," and the 11th is "Nokori Ebisu." During the New Year's Festival, events like lotteries and {{ill|Geisha|ja|芸妓}} processions are famous.

== Access ==
*{{ill|Fukuoka City Subway Hakozaki Line|ja|福岡市地下鉄箱崎線}} {{ill|Chiyo-Kenchōguchi Station|ja|千代県庁口駅}}
*{{ill|Kyushu Railway Company|ja|九州旅客鉄道}} {{ill|Kagoshima Main Line|ja|鹿児島本線}} {{ill|Yoshizuka Station|ja|吉塚駅}}

